Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the deployment and control flow of the ShiftLeftSecurity_traceleft system based on the provided repository summary:

```plantuml
@startuml ShiftLeftSecurity_traceleft

participant "CLI Application" as CLI
participant "Cobra Command Handler" as Cobra
participant "Text Processor" as TextProc
participant "System Interaction Layer" as SysInteract
participant "eBPF Module" as eBPF
participant "File System Watcher" as FSWatcher
participant "YAML Processor" as YAML
participant "Cache" as Cache
participant "Operating System" as OS

CLI -> Cobra: Initialize and parse command
Cobra -> TextProc: Process internationalized text
TextProc -> Cache: Check for cached data
Cache --> TextProc: Return cached data (if available)
TextProc -> SysInteract: Make system call
SysInteract -> OS: Execute system call
OS --> SysInteract: Return system call result
SysInteract --> TextProc: Return processed data
TextProc --> Cobra: Return formatted text

Cobra -> eBPF: Load eBPF program
eBPF -> OS: Interact with kernel
OS --> eBPF: Return kernel data
eBPF --> Cobra: Return processed data

Cobra -> FSWatcher: Watch for file system events
FSWatcher -> OS: Monitor file system
OS --> FSWatcher: Notify of file system event
FSWatcher --> Cobra: Report file system change

Cobra -> YAML: Process configuration
YAML -> Cache: Store processed configuration
Cache --> YAML: Confirm storage
YAML --> Cobra: Return parsed configuration

Cobra --> CLI: Execute command and return result

@enduml
```